Date:  23/9/1933
Source:  Press, The
Author:
Vol / Page:  13
Edition:
Quote:  Sailors [sic] word for porridge. Here the word is applied to the oatmeal and water taken to the woolshed or harvest field to be drunk between smoke-ohs. I have also heard it called <i>beer</i> and <i>brose</i>. (C.)[c1890-1910]
Notes:  Acland Glossary
